        <release version="4.2.0" date="2024-07-16">
            <description>
                <p>Enhancements:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>EEVEE has been completely rewritten from scratch to allow global illumination, displacement, better SSS, viewport motion blur, and more.</li>
                    <li>Cycles has been upgraded to make your renders look better and faster.</li>
                    <li>Add-ons and themes have received a significant overhaul and are now unified as Extensions.</li>
                    <li>A new community-managed website for sharing and discovering Blender extensions.</li>
                    <li>Khronos PBR Neutral Tone Mapper has been added.</li>
                    <li>Polyline has been added to the family of gestures (lasso, box, and line).</li>
                    <li>A new socket type for matrices is available for transformations using nodes.</li>
                    <li>It is now possible to use Node Tools with information about the viewport and mouse position in the node tree.</li>
                    <li>The Video Sequencer has updated its design, tools, and performance.</li>
                    <li>Collections can now specify their own exporters, making it easier to repeatedly export assets, such as glTF or USD, for studio pipelines.</li>
                </ul>
            </description>
        </release>
        <release version="4.1.1" date="2024-04-16"/>
        <release version="4.1.0" date="2024-03-26">
            <description>
                <p>New features:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Geometry nodes can now be baked &amp; New Geometry nodes</li>
                    <li>New Smooth by Angle modifier replaced Auto Smooth</li>
                    <li>OpenImageDenoise is now GPU accelerated</li>
                    <li>A new way for inserting animation keyframes and generating motion paths</li>
                    <li>New graph editor operators &amp; bake channels</li>
                    <li>More USD features &amp; VFX Reference Platform 2024 compliance</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Enhancements:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The viewport compositor now supports more nodes</li>
                    <li>Faster video sequencer with improved image filtering</li>
                    <li>AMD GPU rendering support added for RDNA3 generation APUs</li>
                    <li>Linux CPU rendering performance was improved by about 5% across benchmarks</li>
                    <li>Better bone collections, switch bones while weight painting</li>
                </ul>
            </description>
        </release>
